<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-06-14T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-06-14T16:00:00-05:00" n="846" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d846">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/6913: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Peck</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at
                                Chungking</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-06-14T17:00:00-04:00">June 14,
                                    1939—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>102. Your 371, June 10, 9 a.m., and 372, June 10, 10 a.m.,<note n="87" xml:id="d846fn87">Latter not printed.</note> in regard to cotton and
                            wheat credits to China. When you next see Arthur Young please ask him to
                            inform the Chinese Minister of Finance that the inquiry made by the
                            Chinese Government is receiving consideration by this Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>